Joe Biden has his work cut out for him as he prepares to be sworn in as the 46th president of the United States. WASHINGTON - Joe Biden is being inaugurated as the 46th President of the United States. Earlier in the day, Biden attended mass at St Matthew's Cathedral in the US capital Washington, D.C. WATCH: Trump leaves the White House Accompanied by his wife Jill, Biden was also joined by Democratic and Republican leaders of Congress in a show of unity ahead of his inauguration. They included Democratic House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Senate minority leader Chuck Schumer, as well as Republican Senate majority leader Mitch McConnell and House Republican leader Kevin McCarthy.